   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (8, 4)\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 150"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Running the initial SCF DFT calculation (~ 1 core hour)\n",
    "\n",
    "Get started:\n",
    "- Go into folder `1_dft_scf`\n",
    "- Insert POTCAR as concatenation of `PAW_PBE Ca_sv`, `PAW_PBE Fe_pv` and `PAW_PBE O`\n",
    "- Goal: get well-converged charge density\n",
    "\n",
    "Input files:\n",
    "- INCAR: large number of steps for good convergence (cheap calculation which will be starting point for future calculations)\n",
    "- POSCAR: CaFeO3 close to experimental low-temperature structure (P21/n symmetry) -> insulating in experiment\n",
    "- KPOINTS: approximately unidistant grid of 7 x 7 x 5\n",
    "\n",
    "Run Vasp with `mpirun -n 8 vasp_std`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dft_energy, dft_dos = np.loadtxt('1_dft_scf/refs/DOSCAR', skiprows=6, unpack=True, usecols=(0, 1))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0, 0.5, 'DOS (1/eV)')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 10,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fermi_energy = 4.63 # can be read from DOSCAR header or OUTCAR\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "ax.plot(dft_energy-4.63, dft_dos)\n",
    "ax.axhline(0, c='k')\n",
    "ax.axvline(0, c='k')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Energy relative to Fermi energy (eV)')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('DOS (1/eV)')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The DOS contains (can be checked with partial DOS):\n",
    "- split Fe-eg bands in the range 0.5 to 4 eV\n",
    "- mainly Fe-t2g bands between -1.5 and 0.5 eV\n",
    "- mainly O-p bands between -7 and -1.5 eV\n",
    "- hybridization between Fe-t2g and O-p\n",
    "\n",
    "Ways DFT gets the system wrong:\n",
    "- system is in low-spin configuration: four d electrons in t2gs instead of 3 in t2gs and 1 in egs\n",
    "- system is metallic instead of insulating\n",
    "\n",
    "Because of t2g contribuations in the O-p-dominated energy range, we use the whole energy range shown to define the correlated subspace via the projectors."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},

    "- Explain CSC principle (shortly), how Vasp works in CSC mode (vasp.lock) and what GAMMA file does\n",
    "- Run with `mpirun -n 32 python3 uni_dmft.py`\n",
    "- Discuss output and results: occupations, energies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "energies = []\n",
    "doss = []\n",
    "for imp in range(4):\n",
    "    data = np.loadtxt(f'2_dmft_csc/refs/pdos_0_{imp}.dat', unpack=True)\n",
    "    energies.append(data[0])\n",
    "    doss.append(data[1:])\n",
    "    \n",
    "energies = np.array(energies)\n",
    "doss = np.array(doss)"
   ]
